com.assylias.jbloomberg

Enum SessionState

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<SessionState>
      • com.assylias.jbloomberg.SessionState
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<SessionState>

    public enum SessionState
extends Enum<SessionState>
    SessionState is an enum representing the possible states of a BloombergSession and its underlying Bloomberg Session. The typical lifecycle is as follows:
    NEW -> STARTING -> CONNECTION_UP -> STARTED -> CONNECTION_DOWN -> TERMINATED

    If the connection is lost and recovered (because SessionOptions.setAutoRestartOnDisconnection(boolean) has been set to true in the SessionOptions), the events will be:
    CONNECTION_DOWN -> CONNECTION_UP

    Note that even if the CONNECTION_UP signal is sent, the session will not return anything until the user is logged on the local machine if using the local Bloomberg terminal as a data source.

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      CONNECTION_DOWN
      Indicates that the BloombergSession has been started and the connection was subsequently lost or the session stopping sequence has started.
      CONNECTION_UP
      Indicates that the BloombergSession's connection is up and running - note that it may not be immediately available for request submissions.
      NEW
      Indicates that the BloombergSession object has been instantiated but its BloombergSession.start() method has not been called yet.
      STARTED
      Indicates that the BloombergSession has been started and can be used.
      STARTING
      Indicates that the BloombergSession is in the process of being started (its BloombergSession.start() method has been called but the connection is not established yet).
      STARTUP_FAILURE
      Indicates that the BloombergSession could not be started - if the BloombergSession.start(java.util.function.Consumer) method has been used, an exception has been passed to the provided Consumer.
      TERMINATED
      Indicates that the BloombergSession has been stopped - it can't be used any longer and can't be restarted.
